        <name>start</name>
        <qualifiedname>CANProtocol::start</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Start the CAN peripheral and apply registered filters. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Must be called after <ref refid="namespaceSTM32Board_1a3785a13cc5ed58de231b71fd5e143f00" kindref="member">STM32Board::begin()</ref> and after all filter and callback registrations. Always adds CTRL_BCAST, TEST_SEQ, and SYNC_REQ to the active filter — mandatory for all nodes, cannot be excluded.</para>
<para>Fires the onStatusChange callback with NORMAL on success. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
