      <memberdef kind="function" id="namespaceCANProtocol_1a1b3df3a100c42b658b0145c597019556" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>NodeHealthPayload</type>
        <definition>NodeHealthPayload CANProtocol::makeNodeHealthPayload</definition>
        <argsstring>(uint8_t nodeId, int8_t dieTempC, NodeFaultCode fault=NodeFaultCode::NONE)</argsstring>
        <name>makeNodeHealthPayload</name>
        <qualifiedname>CANProtocol::makeNodeHealthPayload</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>uint8_t</type>
          <declname>nodeId</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int8_t</type>
          <declname>dieTempC</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="NodeStatus_8h_1ad46bdfb956f3738768ac20fb36e8daf1" kindref="member">NodeFaultCode</ref></type>
          <declname>fault</declname>
          <defval><ref refid="NodeStatus_8h_1ad46bdfb956f3738768ac20fb36e8daf1ab50339a10e1de285ac99d4c3990b8693" kindref="member">NodeFaultCode::NONE</ref></defval>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Build the 8-byte node-health payload for the current node. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The CAN/DCS packing boundary: takes the internal die temperature (via <ref refid="namespaceSTM32Board_1a7d2ec3789c2b1dd22bd0bec6c1064b89" kindref="member">STM32Board::readDieTempC()</ref>) and the node&apos;s aggregated fault (via NodeStatus::aggregateFaults()) and packs them into a NodeHealthPayload. Sets the overheat flag (bit0) only when NODE_OVERHEAT_C is defined and dieTempC meets it; sets the DEGRADED flag (bit1) and faultId when <computeroutput>fault</computeroutput> is not NONE (the enum→byte cast happens here). faultMask + reserved bytes stay 0.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>nodeId</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Node ID (1-63 <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup" kindref="compound">PanelGroup</ref>; 0 <ref refid="namespacePanelBridge" kindref="compound">PanelBridge</ref>). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dieTempC</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Internal die temp in whole °C (INT8_MIN = unavailable). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fault</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Aggregated node fault (<ref refid="NodeStatus_8h_1ad46bdfb956f3738768ac20fb36e8daf1ab50339a10e1de285ac99d4c3990b8693" kindref="member">NodeFaultCode::NONE</ref> = healthy). Default NONE. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Fully populated NodeHealthPayload ready to send as HEALTH_n. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
